\b 14. Explain Ozone depletion\par
\b0 Most atmospheric ozone is concentrated in a layer in the stratosphere, about 15 to 30 km above the Earth's surface.\par
Ozone is a molecule that contains three oxygen atoms. \par
At any given time, ozone molecules are constantly formed and destroyed in the stratosphere\par
Ozone is good at trapping a type of radiation called ultraviolet radiation, or UV light\par
\par
The main cause of ozone depletion and the ozone hole is manufactured chemicals, \par
especially manufactured halocarbon refrigerants, solvents, propellants, \par
and foam- blowing agents (chlorofluorocarbons (CFCs), HCFCs, halons)\par
\par
- UVB causes non-melanoma skin cancer and plays a major role in malignant melanoma development\par
