\b 15. What is Green House Effect ?\par
\b0 The greenhouse effect is a natural process that warms the Earth's surface. When the Sun's energy reaches the Earth's atmosphere, \par
some of it is reflected back to space and the rest is absorbed and re-radiated by greenhouse gases such as CO2\par
\par
- Due to Green house effect, there is life exists on earth.\par
\par
- The major contributors to the greenhouses gases are factories, automobiles, deforestation, etc. \par
\par
The increased number of factories and automobiles increases the amount of these gases in the atmosphere. The greenhouse gases \par
never let the radiations escape from the earth and increase the surface temperature of the earth. This then leads to global warming.\par
